The predecessor <i>uvc-streamer</i> is working well, but i wanted to implement a few more ideas. For instance, plugins can be used to process the images. One input plugin copies images to a global variable, multiple output plugins can access those images. It\'s designed for reduced lag.</li>\n  <li>Use Firefox and Opus audio. Opus is the next-gen low-latency low-bandwidth codec audio streaming codec and Firefox does little buffering of it.</li>\n  <li>Use VLC Media Player. In it\'s menu, open Media \u21e8 Open Network Stream, enter http://your-ip:your-port/audio.wav as the URL, click "Show more options" and set buffering to 1 ms.</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n \n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-footer">\n        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>\n      </div>\n    </div><!-- /.modal-content -->\n  </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->\n</div><!-- /.modal -->\n\n<div id="explain_tasker" class="modal fade">\n  <div class="modal-dialog">\n    <div class="modal-content">\n      <div class="modal-header">\n        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">x</button>\n        <h4>Tasker events control</h4>\n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-body">\n        <p><a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.dinglisch.android.taskerm">Tasker</a> is an automation solution for Android smartphones. It can help you, for example, send an SMS or change ringer volume based on your location or by the schedule.</p>\n <p>IP Webcam Pro can generate Tasker events, either with web interface or with customizable UI.</p>\n <p>To configure Tasker for using IP Webcam events, create a new Profile using &quot;+&quot; button and select State \u21e8 Plugin \u21e8 IP Webcam as a trigger.</p>\n <p>Events generated from web interface have the same event name as the button text. For example, the central button generates the event named &quot;5&quot;.</p>\n <p/>\n \n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-footer">\n        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>\n      </div>\n    </div><!-- /.modal-content -->\n  </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->\n</div><!-- /.modal -->\n\n<div id="explain_https" class="modal fade">\n  <div class="modal-dialog">\n    <div class="modal-content">\n      <div class="modal-header">\n        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">x</button>\n        <h4>Warning when using HTTPS?</h4>\n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-body">\n        <p>Getting HTTPS warning is normal when the host is not accessed using DNS.</p>\n <p>Using HTTPS still protects from eavesdropper attacks when using insecure networks.</p>\n <p>It\'s safe to ignore these warnings.</p>\n \n        <br/>\n        <p>Navigate to <a id="https_target"></a></p>\n \n\n<div id="explain_audio" class="modal fade">\n  <div class="modal-dialog">\n    <div class="modal-content">\n      <div class="modal-header">\n        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">x</button>\n        <h4>Why do I hear the audio 4 seconds late?</h4>\n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-body">\n        <p>This happens due to browser buffering and depends on the browser used.</p>\n <p>Try these solutions:</p>\n <ul>\n  <li>Use Flash renderer. It\'s designed for reduced lag.</li>\n  <li>Use Firefox and Opus audio. Opus is the next-gen low-latency low-bandwidth codec audio streaming codec and Firefox does little buffering of it.</li>\n  <li>Use VLC Media Player. In it\'s menu, open Media \u21e8 Open Network Stream, enter http://your-ip:your-port/audio.wav as the URL, click "Show more options" and set buffering to 1 ms.</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n \n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-footer">\n        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>\n      </div>\n    </div><!-- /.modal-content -->\n  </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->\n</div><!-- /.modal -->\n\n<div id="explain_tasker" class="modal fade">\n  <div class="modal-dialog">\n    <div class="modal-content">\n      <div class="modal-header">\n        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">x</button>\n        <h4>Tasker events control</h4>\n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-body">\n        <p><a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.dinglisch.android.taskerm">Tasker</a> is an automation solution for Android smartphones. It can help you, for example, send an SMS or change ringer volume based on your location or by the schedule.</p>\n <p>IP Webcam Pro can generate Tasker events, either with web interface or with customizable UI.</p>\n <p>To configure Tasker for using IP Webcam events, create a new Profile using &quot;+&quot; button and select State \u21e8 Plugin \u21e8 IP Webcam as a trigger.</p>\n <p>Events generated from web interface have the same event name as the button text. For example, the central button generates the event named &quot;5&quot;.</p>\n <p/>\n \n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-footer">\n        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" Opus est la prochaine g\xe9n\xe9ration \xe0 faible latence et faible bande passante de codec audio en streaming et Firefox ne fait pas de m\xe9moire tampon de lui.</li>\n  <li>Utilisez VLC Media Player. C\'est dans son menu, ouvrez M\xe9dia \u21e8 Ouvrir un flux r\xe9seau, entrez http://votre-ip:votre-port/audio.wav comme URL, puis cliquez sur "Afficher plus d\'optiosn" et s\xe9lectionnez "Mise en cache" et entrez 1 ms.</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n \n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-footer">\n        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Fermer</button>\n      </div>\n    </div><!-- /.modal-content -->\n  </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->\n</div><!-- /.modal -->\n\n<div id="explain_tasker" class="modal fade">\n  <div class="modal-dialog">\n    <div class="modal-content">\n      <div class="modal-header">\n        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">x</button>\n        <h4>Tasker contr\xf4le des \xe9v\xe9nements</h4>\n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-body">\n        <p><a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.dinglisch.android.taskerm">Tasker</a> est une solution d\'automatisation pour les smartphones Android. Il peut vous aider, par exemple, \xe0 envoyer un SMS ou de modifier le volume de la sonnerie en fonction de votre emplacement ou de l\'heure.</p>\n <p>IP Webcam Pro peut g\xe9n\xe9rer des \xe9v\xe8nements Tasker, soit avec l\'interface Web ou avec l\'interface utilisateur personnalisable.</p>\n <p>Pour configurer Tasker pour utiliser les \xe9v\xe8nements IP Webcam, cr\xe9ez un nouveau profil en utilisant le bouton &quot;+&quot; et s\xe9lectionnez Etat \u21e8 Plugin \u21e8 IP Webcam comme un d\xe9clencheur.</p>\n <p>Les \xe9v\xe9nements g\xe9n\xe9r\xe9s \xe0 partir de l\'interface web ont le m\xeame nom de l\'\xe9v\xe9nement que le texte du bouton. Par exemple, le bouton central g\xe9n\xe8re l\'\xe9v\xe9nement nomm\xe9 &quot;5&quot;.</p>\n <p/>\n \n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-footer">\n        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Fermer</button>\n      </div>\n    </div><!-- /.modal-content -->\n  </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->\n</div><!-- /.modal -->\n\n<div id="explain_https" class="modal fade">\n  <div class="modal-dialog">\n    <div class="modal-content">\n      <div class="modal-header">\n        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">x</button>\n        <h4>Warning when using HTTPS?</h4>\n      </div>\n      <div class="modal-body">\n        <p>Getting HTTPS warning is normal when the host is not accessed using DNS.</p>\n <p>Using HTTPS still protects from eavesdropper attacks when using insecure networks.</p>\n <p>It\'s safe to ignore these warnings.</p>\n \n        <br/>\n        <p>Navigate to <a With 5.x after 5.6.28 or 7.x after 7.0.13, the issue is resolved in a non-default configuration with the opcache.validate_permission=1 setting. The vulnerability details are as follows. In PHP SAPIs where PHP interpreters share a common parent process, Zend OpCache creates a shared memory object owned by the common parent during initialization. Child PHP processes inherit the SHM descriptor, using it to cache and retrieve compiled script bytecode ("opcode" in PHP jargon). Cache keys vary depending on configuration, but filename is a central key component, and compiled opcode can generally be run if a script\'s filename is known or can be guessed. Many common shared-hosting configurations change EUID in child processes to enforce privilege separation among hosted users (for example using mod_ruid2 for the Apache HTTP Server, or php-fpm user settings). In these scenarios, the default Zend OpCache behavior defeats script file permissions by sharing a single SHM cache among all child PHP processes. u'5.0', u'summary': u"Apache httpd allows remote attackers to read secret data from process memory if the Limit directive can be set in a user's .htaccess file, or if httpd.conf has certain misconfigurations, aka Optionsbleed. If the header value is not present in the charset conversion table, a fallback mechanism is used to truncate it to a two characters value to allow a quick retry (for example, 'en-US' is truncated to 'en'). A header value of less than two characters forces an out of bound write of one NUL byte to a memory location that is not part of the string. In the worst case, quite unlikely, the process would crash which could be used as a Denial of Service attack. The user hears a brief introduction and begins playing clips to the user.</span></li>\n            <li class="list-group-item"><span>The clips are short, (~30 secs) taken from a full clip a band has uploaded into the system.</span></li>\n            <li class="list-group-item"><span>After each clip, the user will give their reaction. If they <strong>didn\'t</strong> like the clip, they will move on to another clip.</span></li>\n            <li class="list-group-item"><span>If they <strong>do</strong> like the clip, they can hear the full song, decide to follow the band, blast the band out onto Facebook, etc</span></li>\n            <li class="list-group-item"><span>Once a user follows a band, they opt in to notifications. They give their mobile phone number and possibly their email address.The next time a new track is released or a show is announced, the band can send out a text message to keep fans updated about what\'s going on!</span></li>\n            <li\n            class="list-group-item"><span>If a band has the album up for sale somewhere online, the user will also have an option to "Buy the Album", and Band Hero can text the user a link to purchase the album. If there isn\'t any album for sale, the band will be notified that a fan wanted to buy an album, but couldn\'t.</span></li>\n        </ul>\n    </section>\n    <section class="features">\n        <div class="container">\n            <div class="row">\n                <div class="col-md-6">\n                    <h2>Fantastic Features</h2></div>\n                <div class="col-md-12">\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Up to 3 Tracks per Band (Maybe more in future)</li>\n                        <li>Give a background story for a track</li>\n                        <li>Specify tags for a track to make them searchable</li>\n                        <li>Specifyband hometown for local discovery</li>\n                        <li>See the stats for each track: plays, likes, dislikes, shares</li>\n                        <li>Blast announcements out to all fans at once via SMS (Test Message)</li>\n           ', u'asn': u'AS62567', u'transport': u'tcp', u'ip_str': u'107.170.76.127'}

A header value of less than two characters forces an out of bound write of one NUL byte to a memory location that is not part of the string. The user hears a brief introduction and begins playing clips to the user.</span></li>\n            <li class="list-group-item"><span>The clips are short, (~30 secs) taken from a full clip a band has uploaded into the system.</span></li>\n            <li class="list-group-item"><span>After each clip, the user will give their reaction. If they <strong>didn\'t</strong> like the clip, they will move on to another clip.</span></li>\n            <li class="list-group-item"><span>If they <strong>do</strong> like the clip, they can hear the full song, decide to follow the band, blast the band out onto Facebook, etc</span></li>\n            <li class="list-group-item"><span>Once a user follows a band, they opt in to notifications. They give their mobile phone number and possibly their email address.The next time a new track is released or a show is announced, the band can send out a text message to keep fans updated about what\'s going on!</span></li>\n            <li\n            class="list-group-item"><span>If a band has the album up for sale somewhere online, the user will also have an option to "Buy the Album", and Band Hero can text the user a link to purchase the album. If there isn\'t any album for sale, the band will be notified that a fan wanted to buy an album, but couldn\'t.</span></li>\n        </ul>\n    </section>\n    <section class="features">\n        <div class="container">\n            <div class="row">\n                <div class="col-md-6">\n                    <h2>Fantastic Features</h2></div>\n                <div class="col-md-12">\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Up to 3 Tracks per Band (Maybe more in future)</li>\n                        <li>Give a background story for a track</li>\n                        <li>Specify tags for a track to make them searchable</li>\n                        <li>Specifyband hometown for local discovery</li>\n                        <li>See the stats for each track: plays, likes, dislikes, shares</li>\n                        <li>Blast announcements out to all fans at once via SMS (Test Message)</li>\n             ', u'asn': u'AS62567', u'transport': u'tcp', u'ip_str': u'192.241.240.144'}

Deutschland?</h2>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<H3>Dann besuchen Sie unsere deutsche Webseite.</h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="cta-button">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class="button" href="/">Jetzt wechseln</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Um Produkte und Leistungen bestellen zu k&ouml;nnen, m&uuml;ssen Sie Ihre jeweilige L&auml;nderversion ausw&auml;hlen. Befinden Sie sich derzeit in Deutschland, w&auml;hlen Sie bitte DE, in &Ouml;sterreich AT und au&szlig;erhalb Deutschlands und &Ouml;sterreich INT.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\n\t\t<div class="container lang3">\n\t\t\t<div class="modal"></div>\n\t\t\t<div class="overlay">\n\t\t\t\t<div class="inner">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class="close"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class="wrapper">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="modal-content">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2>Sie kommen aus \xd6sterreich?</h2>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<H3>Dann besuchen Sie unsere \xf6sterreichische Webseite.</h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="cta-button">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class="button" href="/at/">Jetzt wechseln</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Um Produkte und Leistungen bestellen zu k&ouml;nnen, m&uuml;ssen Sie Ihre jeweilige L&auml;nderversion ausw&auml;hlen. Befinden Sie sich derzeit in &Ouml;sterreich, w&auml;hlen Sie bitte AT, in Deutschland&nbsp;DE und au&szlig;erhalb Deutschlands und &Ouml;sterreich INT.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\n\t\t<div class="container lang12">\n\t\t\t<div class="modal"></div>\n\t\t\t<div class="overlay">\n\t\t\t\t<div class="inner">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class="close"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class="wrapper">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="modal-content">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2>Sie befinden sich au\xdferhalb Deutschlands oder \xd6sterreichs?</h2>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<H3>Dann besuchen Sie unsere internationale Webseite.</h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="cta-button">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class="button" href="/int/">Jetzt wechseln</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Um Produkte und Leistungen bestellen zu k&ouml;nnen, m&uuml;ssen Sie Ihre jeweilige L&auml;nderversion ausw&auml;hlen. Befinden Sie sich derzeit au&szlig;erhalb Deutschlands oder &Ouml;sterreichs, w&auml;hlen Sie bitte INT, in &Ouml;sterreich AT und in&nbsp;Deutschland&nbsp;DE.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\n\t</section>\n<!--TYPO3SEARCH_begin-->\n\n\n\t\n\n\n</div>\n\n\n<div id="c21341" class="default-content-element">\n\t\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t<section id="df-footnote" class="df-footnote">\n\t\n\t\t<div class="row">\n\t\t\t<div class="small-12 columns">\n\t\t\t\t<div class="note note0">\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Preis pro Monat, Abrechnungszeitraum 12 Monate. Alle Betr&auml;ge inklusive gesetzlicher Mehrwertsteuer.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\n</section>\n\n\n\t\n\n\n</div>\n\n\n\t\t<!--TYPO3SEARCH_end-->\n\t\n</div>\n<div class="websitebuilder">\n\t<div class="modal"></div>\n\t<div class="overlay">\n\t\t<div class="inner">\n\t\t\t<div class="wrapper">\n\t\t\t\t<p>Bitte haben Sie einen Moment Geduld. With 5.x after 5.6.28 or 7.x after 7.0.13, the issue is resolved in a non-default configuration with the opcache.validate_permission=1 setting. The vulnerability details are as follows. In PHP SAPIs where PHP interpreters share a common parent process, Zend OpCache creates a shared memory object owned by the common parent during initialization. Child PHP processes inherit the SHM descriptor, using it to cache and retrieve compiled script bytecode ("opcode" in PHP jargon). Cache keys vary depending on configuration, but filename is a central key component, and compiled opcode can generally be run if a script\'s filename is known or can be guessed. Many common shared-hosting configurations change EUID in child processes to enforce privilege separation among hosted users (for example using mod_ruid2 for the Apache HTTP Server, or php-fpm user settings). In these scenarios, the default Zend OpCache behavior defeats script file permissions by sharing a single SHM cache among all child PHP processes. PHP scripts often contain sensitive information: Think of CMS configurations where reading or running another user\'s script usually means gaining privileges to the CMS database.'}, u'CVE-2008-0455': style="width:800px">Serviced.co.uk is a comprehensive listing of almost every serviced office in the UK.\n    Unlike most other guides, we list the physical address, website address, and the name of the company operating the office, for example, Regus.\n    Where a location doesn\'t have the operator you are looking for, we will provide you with alternative operators, and tell you where your J\xe4hrlich werden rund 160 bis 180 internationale und nationale Messen mit bis zu 180.000 Ausstellern und rund 10 Mio. Besuchern durchgef\xfchrt. Aus diesem Grund haben wir es uns zum Ziel gesetzt, unseren Kunden in allen wichtigen Destinationen eine gro\xdfe Auswahl an verf\xfcgbaren Hotels anbieten zu k\xf6nnen. Einen \xdcberblick \xfcber unsere derzeit am meist gefragten Destinationen findest du hier: M\xfcnchen: Analytica, IFAT, IBA, Exporeal, Electronica, Bau, Bauma \u2013 D\xfcsseldorf: Wire &amp; Tube, Aluminium, Medica, K-Messe, Euroshop Interpack, Drupa \u2013 K\xf6ln: Anuga, Photokina, IDS \u2013 Frankfurt: Light &amp; Building, Achema, Automechanika, ISH, Ambiente \u2013 Hannover: HMI, IAA, g,h,i,j,k=b.createElement("canvas"),l=k.getContext&&k.getContext("2d");for(j=Array("flag","emoji"),c.supports={everything:!0,everythingExceptFlag:!0},i=0;i<j.length;i++)c.supports[j[i]]=e(j[i]),c.supports.everything=c.supports.everything&&c.supports[j[i]],"flag"!==j[i]&&(c.supports.everythingExceptFlag=c.supports.everythingExceptFlag&&c.supports[j[i]]);c.supports.everythingExceptFlag=c.supports.everythingExceptFlag&&!c.supports.flag,c.DOMReady=!1,c.readyCallback=function(){c.DOMReady=!0},c.supports.everything||(h=function(){c.readyCallback()},b.addEventListener?(b.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded",h,!1),a.addEventListener("load",h,!1)):(a.attachEvent("onload",h),b.attachEvent("onreadystatechange",function(){"complete"===b.readyState&&c.readyCallback()})),g=c.source||{},g.concatemoji?f(g.concatemoji):g.wpemoji&&g.twemoji&&(f(g.twemoji),f(g.wpemoji)))}(window,document,window._wpemojiSettings);\n\t\t</script>\n\t\t<style type="text/css">\nimg.wp-smiley,\nimg.emoji {\n\tdisplay: inline !important;\n\tborder: none !important;\n\tbox-shadow: none !important;\n\theight: 1em !important;\n\twidth: 1em !important;\n\tmargin: class=\'col-control fix\'>\r\n\t<header id="header" class="fix">\r\n\t\t\t<h1 class="blogtitle left"><a href="https://linuxmonk.ch/wordpress">linuxmonk.ch</a></h1>\r\n\t\t<div class="description right">In search of technological enlightment</div>\r\n    </header><!-- /header -->\r\n\t\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t</div><!-- //#header-container -->\r\n \t<nav id="nav" class="continuous fix">\r\n\t\t<div class=\'col-control left\'>\r\n\t<!-- right-header-widgets -->\n\t<div id="right-header-widgets" class="warea">\n\t\r\n<form method="get" class="searchform "
